The paper deals with approximation schemes for geometric set cover and maximum k-coverage problems, which are classic problems in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of planar separator theorem, which is a fundamental tool in algorithm design and analysis, and thus it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the color-balanced version of the planar separator theorem, which is related to graph coloring, and hence it could be categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper involves approximation algorithms, which is a topic in theoretical computer science, and hence it could be categorized under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the use of local search, which is a common technique in optimization and machine learning, and hence it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
